00:00:30.777 --> 00:00:34.078
- Good afternoon, everyone, and welcome.

00:00:34.078 --> 00:00:35.537
My name is Gibor Basri.

00:00:35.537 --> 00:00:38.697
I'm a professor of the
graduate school in astronomy

00:00:38.697 --> 00:00:41.839
and the former Vice Chancellor
of Equity &amp; Inclusion

00:00:41.839 --> 00:00:45.238
and a member of the Hitchcock
Professorship Committee.

00:00:45.238 --> 00:00:47.244
We're very pleased along
with the Graduate Council

00:00:47.244 --> 00:00:51.172
to present to you this
afternoon Nina Jablonski,

00:00:51.172 --> 00:00:52.456
who is this spring's speaker

00:00:52.456 --> 00:00:56.535
in the Charles M. and Martha
Hitchcock Lecture Series.

00:00:56.535 --> 00:01:00.868
As a condition of the bequest
I am obliged but happy

00:01:00.868 --> 00:01:03.561
to give you some of the verbal information

00:01:03.561 --> 00:01:07.370
that is also in your
program about the endowment

00:01:07.370 --> 00:01:08.909
