01:00:00.178 --> 01:00:01.638
I didn't plant you in the audience

01:00:01.638 --> 01:00:04.579
but I'm so glad that
you asked that question.

01:00:04.579 --> 01:00:08.746
People always ask me about the
dark pigmentation of Inuit.

01:00:10.495 --> 01:00:13.561
Inuit and many of the circumpolar peoples

01:00:13.561 --> 01:00:15.460
have great tanning ability.

01:00:15.460 --> 01:00:18.543
When you look at their unexposed skin

01:00:19.482 --> 01:00:22.093
it's sort of moderately pigmented,

01:00:22.093 --> 01:00:26.412
but they have tremendous
ability to make melanin

01:00:26.412 --> 01:00:31.073
in their skin as a result
of direct solar radiation,

01:00:31.073 --> 01:00:35.406
but also from UV that
bounces off the surface

01:00:35.406 --> 01:00:37.906
of the water and snow and ice.

01:00:40.136 --> 01:00:42.787
So how do they manage?

01:00:42.787 --> 01:00:45.122
So here they are, super high latitudes,

01:00:45.122 --> 01:00:49.596
Arctic Circle and above,
how do they manage?

01:00:49.596 --> 01:00:53.763
They get their vitamin D
entirely through their diet.

01:00:54.886 --> 01:00:59.560
And when we look at the
culture of Inuit people

01:00:59.560 --> 01:01:03.375
it is built around the harvesting
of vitamin D-rich food.

01:01:03.375 --> 01:01:07.042
Whether we're talking
about spearing whales,

01:01:08.130 --> 01:01:09.797
or seals, sea lions,

01:01:11.772 --> 01:01:14.238
or eating oily fish,

01:01:14.238 --> 01:01:15.896
or in the hinterland

01:01:15.896 --> 01:01:17.813
chasing caribou or reindeer,

01:01:17.813 --> 01:01:21.281
depending on which part
of the Arctic you're in.

01:01:21.281 --> 01:01:25.043
You are pursuing vitamin D-rich prey.

01:01:25.043 --> 01:01:29.001
And basically people can
maintain good health,

01:01:29.001 --> 01:01:33.953
Inuit people, when they are
eating vitamin D-rich foods.

01:01:33.953 --> 01:01:37.116
As soon as they start
moving to settlements

01:01:37.116 --> 01:01:39.993
and abandon their traditional diet

01:01:39.993 --> 01:01:43.880
they have terrific problems
of vitamin D deficiency,

01:01:43.880 --> 01:01:45.243
which are now a cause

01:01:45.243 --> 01:01:48.954
of great public health
concern and mitigation.

01:01:48.954 --> 01:01:53.068
But the fascinating thing
is that natural selection

01:01:53.068 --> 01:01:56.823
has worked to enhance
tanning through genes,

01:01:56.823 --> 01:01:59.629
complexes that we still don't understand.

01:01:59.629 --> 01:02:04.520
Enhanced tanning to protect
against this UVA load

01:02:04.520 --> 01:02:08.201
in a sense knowing that the vitamin D

01:02:08.201 --> 01:02:10.784
is coming from dietary sources.

