01:04:14.215 --> 01:04:16.809
was something other than
evaporative cooling?

01:04:16.809 --> 01:04:19.636
- Oh, yes, very good question.

01:04:19.636 --> 01:04:23.053
So with our hairy ancestors and relatives

01:04:24.026 --> 01:04:26.443
modern monkeys and apes today

01:04:27.774 --> 01:04:31.357
actually lose body heat
through their skin,

01:04:33.029 --> 01:04:34.964
through their hairy skin,

01:04:34.964 --> 01:04:37.804
and they have some sweat glands.

01:04:37.804 --> 01:04:40.401
So they are able to sweat a little bit.

01:04:40.401 --> 01:04:43.038
There are some monkeys,

01:04:43.038 --> 01:04:47.078
the patas monkey of east and west Africa

01:04:47.078 --> 01:04:49.489
has a relatively thin coat of hair

01:04:49.489 --> 01:04:52.361
and quite a few eccrine sweat glands.

01:04:52.361 --> 01:04:56.528
It is the most fast-running
