01:04:57.626 --> 01:05:01.764
and people have looked at the patas monkey

01:05:01.764 --> 01:05:04.931
as sort of a model for human sweating.

01:05:06.487 --> 01:05:09.838
That there was natural
selection for thinning of hair

01:05:09.838 --> 01:05:13.411
and increased density
of eccrine sweat glands.

01:05:13.411 --> 01:05:16.476
But the key thing with
all of these primates

01:05:16.476 --> 01:05:18.329
is that they did lose heat

01:05:18.329 --> 01:05:20.948
through the surfaces of their body.

01:05:20.948 --> 01:05:23.568
There isn't a specialized
panting mechanism

01:05:23.568 --> 01:05:27.485
or nasal-cooling mechanism
as in other mammals.

